Name:          Marie Curie
Lived:         1867 - 1934
Nationality:   Polish-French
Field:         Chemistry/Physics
Known For:     Radioactivity
Contribution:  First woman Nobel laureate; Nobel in two sciences; discovered radium and polonium
Quote:         "Nothing in life is to be feared, only to be understood."

Name:          William Shakespeare
Lived:         1564 - 1616
Nationality:   English
Field:         Literature
Known For:     Hamlet, Romeo and Juliet
Contribution:  38 plays; 154 sonnets; invented 1,700+ English words
Quote:         "All the world's a stage."

Name:          Galileo Galilei
Lived:         1564 - 1642
Nationality:   Italian
Field:         Astronomy
Known For:     Heliocentrism, telescope
Contribution:  Confirmed Copernican model; law of falling bodies; faced Inquisition
Quote:         "And yet it moves."

